Hilary Wilson had a cardiac arrest during a Caesarean section and 'died' for 11 minutes . 
  She woke up four days later with no memory of being pregnant or having her son Felix . 
  The 41-year-old suffered an amniotic fluid embolism and was technically dead . 
  She was given just a 30 per cent chance of survival and 85 per cent of brain damage . 
  She only realised she had a son when she saw a picture of him wearing her children's hand-me-downs . 
  Mrs Wilson had no idea she had been pregnant or given birth to her son . 
 